    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As I understand it, this was done on purpose in status-go to prevent spam. \n\nThe reason this occurs is because when Device B leaves the group, it remains a member of the chat, but the chat is marked as `active: false` (which means it not visible to or cannot be interacted with by Device B). If Device B was removed as a member, then it would work as desired. This logic may be reverted when the \"swipe to delete\" feature is included in mobile, as mentioned by @cammellos.\n\nAdditionally, when a user is re-invited in Step 4, there is an activity center notification received on Device B's side that looks like the following:\n```json\n\"activityCenterNotifications\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"0x0e342d33\",\n        \"chatId\": \"e342d33f-dd05-4d7b-b14e-b5335e1a3ee9-0x043bf46aa874c377a34946eab67a32cf36c15907b328216dfce375d169fed7d81c21cada3229db1fd37c762d2c02702111a646657feca6621e2e948febcf378fb4\",\n        \"name\": \"test-22\",\n        \"type\": 2,\n        \"lastMessage\": null,\n        \"message\": null,\n        \"timestamp\": 1623305612000,\n        \"read\": false,\n        \"dismissed\": false,\n        \"accepted\": false\n      }\n    ]\n```\nThere is a possibility that when accepting this notification in the Activity Center, it may allow the user to be re-invited, however since the Activity Center feature hasn't been finished yet on desktop, I'm unable to test that theory.",
